01/06/2004
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- The president of the World Association of Newspapers on Monday (31 May) praised Turkey for the significant progress it has made in expanding freedom of expression. Seok Hyun Hong added that holding the 57th World Newspaper Congress and 11th World Editors Forum in Istanbul bore testimony to Turkey's success in this area. Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan pledged his government's resolve to continue to expand freedom of the press, and asked members of the European media to support his country's EU membership bid.
In other news, Turkish President Ahmet Necdet Sezer is in Poland. He will meet with his counterpart, Aleksander Kwasniewski, on Tuesday. Talks will focus on bilateral relations, as well as on co-operation within NATO structures and within regional and international contexts. (Hurriyet - 01/06/04; AP, Anadolu Agency, TRT 2, Turkish Daily News - 31/05/04)
